# Portfolio Project PRD (Product Requirements Document)

## Project Overview
A modern remake of an existing resume/portfolio website, https://github.com/brettwhite-git/resume, rebuilt from the ground up using cutting-edge technologies and design principles. This project aims to showcase professional experience and skills through a minimalistic, design-forward interface while maintaining exceptional performance and responsiveness.

## Core Technologies & Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js 14+ with React 18+
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS
- **UI Components**: shadcn/ui component library
- **Deployment**: Vercel
- **TypeScript**: Full type safety throughout the application
- **Performance**: Optimized for Core Web Vitals and accessibility

## Technical Requirements
- **Performance**: Lighthouse score 90+ across all metrics
- **Accessibility**: WCAG 2.1 AA compliance
- **SEO**: Optimized meta tags, structured data, and semantic HTML
- **Mobile-First**: Responsive design starting from 320px viewport
- **Browser Support**: Modern browsers (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge)
- **Loading Speed**: Initial page load under 2 seconds
- **Compile Errors**: Make sure there are no linter nor build errors as complete milestones

## Design Philosophy
- **Minimalistic**: Clean, uncluttered layouts with purposeful whitespace
- **Modern**: Contemporary design patterns and typography
- **Design-Forward**: Visual hierarchy, thoughtful color palettes, and micro-interactions
- **Shadcn**: Work with shadcn components, cards, charts, themes and colors as necessary before adding other pacakages. Cards/ charts/ divs should respect the side bar and neighbor components with equivalant spacing. 
- **Responsive**: Mobile-first approach with seamless cross-device experiences
- **Performance-Optimized**: Fast loading times, optimized images, and efficient code splitting


